🧪 Wiring Overview BME280 / BMP280 (I²C Mode) VIN → 3.3V

GND → GND

SCL → GPIO 22

SDA → GPIO 21

MQ Gas Sensor (Analog Mode) VCC → 5V

GND → GND

A0 → GPIO 34 (ADC input)

Notes MQ sensors require 5V heating, but output is analog and safe for ESP32 ADC.

Use a voltage divider if your MQ module outputs >3.3V on A0.

BME280 and BMP280 can share the same I²C bus.

. Install PlatformIO PlatformIO is recommended for building and uploading firmware.

